Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the design of error-correcting codes, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity of the designed codes and aims to reduce it. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - Error-correcting codes are important in networking and internet architecture to ensure reliable transmission of data. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper may be relevant to the design of error-correcting codes for communication in social and information networks. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new method for designing error-correcting codes, which may involve the use of algorithms and data structures.
